      ],
      "range": [
        45,
        63
      ],
      "target": "figure_41fe7709fd0c1c53e1c5db05fb871882"
    },
    "text_8319dccee2025e5f586aebb6c7dbd9bd": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_8319dccee2025e5f586aebb6c7dbd9bd",
      "source_id": "",
      "content": "Substance documents are just regular zip archives. Once extracted they look like shown above. A. The content.json file stores the actual content and structure of your documents. B. The index.html file starts a Subtance Reader instance, and enables you publish your documents online. It works with any webserver. C. Substance documents are self-contained and store the assets such as images in regular binary files."
    },
